BTW, this sort of &#39;first crawl&#39; stuff is well explained in the Doc page:

https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/A+Quick+Guide+to+Running+Your+First+Crawl+Job

Unfortunately it looks like something, maybe a wiki software upgrade, 
has jumbled the original ordering of the pages under...
https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Heritrix+3.0+and+3.1+User+Guide
...but there&#39;s still a ton of good info there.

We&#39;ve tried to give a general idea of the available settings values via 
the comments in the example CXML doc. Major options of various 
components are documented in other topic-specific wiki pages, but to 
know *every* option does require reviewing the source code or 
developers&#39; &#39;JavaDoc&#39; -- because the CXML format (adopted from Spring 
beans.xml) lets you poke about any value into any variable/method of all 
the underlying code.

- Gordon

